blog.description: rep Tour Toronto 3/8/2018! I’ve said it before, I’ll say it again; I love Taylor Swift with my WHOLE HEART

body:
They don’t know her

I was having a heated discussion about Taylor and her character. I was talking about all the good stuff that she’s done and they were like “she probably did that for attention” or “it was set up” or even “she wanted to protect her reputation” and the thing is like,,, maybe she did? Those could be reasons for anyone to do anything, though.

That’s the thing. You will never really know someone’s true intentions. You can trust them, though. And I trust Taylor.

We could argue forever but what’s the use? I know why I’m fighting this. Because she means the world to me. I know why they’re fighting this. Because they want to torment me without knowing why she means so much to me.

They don’t know her, and technically neither do I. But they don’t know her the way I do. She’s never noticed me, but it feels like we’re close friends. I can tell her anything, she can tell me anything, and there’s just this good mutual trust that we have goin on. Even though we’ve never met.

I shouldn’t let what other people say about Taylor because they already have their minds made up, but it kind of feels like a personal attack.

As Taylor said herself “call it what you want” so really they can think what they want, but I know what she means to me, and that’s what matters.
